HEADWORD: Carvist
<hw>Car"vist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[A corruption of
<ets>carry fist</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Falconary)</fld> <def>A hawk which
is of proper age and training to be carried on the hand; a hawk in its
first year.</def> <rj><au>Booth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

